1.title: Pilot
1.plot: Robbaz is creating his first characters - King and Clyde. He builds them their first trailer and outlines their style of living - BBQ, guns and breaking into neighbors' houses.

2.title: Brokeback Redneck
2.plot: Robbaz adds 2 more trailers to Redneck family. We meet Barry Tenderlove, King's boss, for the first time. First appearance of the cult character Bertram the Butler.

3.title: Generous Neighbors
3.plot: Clyde robs a family, kills all the members of it and plays table soccer with the Grim. More trailers are added, and a wedding turns failure.

4.title: Corgipupalypse
4.plot: King and Clyde adopt 2 corgis and build them a luxurious trailer home. While Bertram experiences anxiety, a pool and a torture dungeon are being built. Corgis have a little pup, Bertram nearly burns the house down.

5.title: The Band
5.plot: Robbaz creates the perfect match for Clyde - Peggy. Another trailer is built, Bertram carries on with his anxiety. King takes his and Barry's relationship to another level and the whole family starts a band. Clyde kidnaps his first victim - Vladimir.

6.title: The Perfect Murican
6.plot: Robbaz decides to build a dining room - a place where the whole family comes together. King adopts a kid and conducts an experiment: the child does nothing, but eats all sorts of junk food, while Barry does nothing, but trains. Bertram's misfortunes finally end in the saddest moment in the series history yet. Another butler Gustavo is employed. Floyd - poor adopted child - has his first birthday in this toxic household, but his misery doesn't end.

7.title: The Alien Abduction
7.plot: Vladimir finally meets his fate. Floyd is being set free from his food prison. Now he is a full functioning member of the family. Clyde finds himself a new hobby - collecting rocks and minerals. Poor Barry can't properly control his oversized biceps and falls victim for alien abduction. He returns with a little baby bump and later gives birth to a beautiful alien baby girl - Billie Jean. Clyde kills again.

8.title: The Motel
8.plot: Floyd is abducted. The beginning of the infamous Roadkill Motel and Diner. Aliens got the taste of the human rednecks, now they can't let go - King is being abducted as well. As the owner of the motel, Clyde takes pictures of the sleeping residents and steals their cars. A supposed pedophile attack makes Clyde pick up his gun again. And again on the next day to avenge his probed relatives, when in the dark of night one reckless alien decides to pay a visit. Billie Jean is a full grown adult now.

9.title: The Resurrection
9.plot: Unfortunate bankruptcy of the Motel leads to it's closing. Bertram becomes a restless ghost, which motivates King to excel in gardening to bring the butler back. Another alien gets himself killed. No trespassers. King catches the deathfish. All those efforts are not in vain - Bertram is now alive. Yet since no one saw his resurrection, he becomes a painting slave in a dungeon right under his grave.

10.title: Love, Death and Art
10.plot: Another wedding is set, ending in passing of two corgis. Peggy gives birth in the rain to a girl Britney. Bertram can't stop painting, all the pictures go to the walls of the dining room, making it an exquisite gallery.

imdb.title: Redneck Brothers
plot: The series tells the story and adventures of 2 redneck brothers King and Clyde.::VPop
